{"parse":{"title":"Perpetual student","pageid":156984,"revid":859901099,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>A <b>perpetual student</b> or <b>career student</b> is a college or <a href=\"/wiki/University\" title=\"University\">university</a> attendee who re-enrolls for several years more than is necessary to obtain a given <a href=\"/wiki/Academic_degree\" title=\"Academic degree\">degree</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Examples\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Examples</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Portrayal_in_media\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Portrayal in media</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Further_reading\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Further reading</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Examples\">Examples</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Perpetual_student&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Examples\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Johnny_Lechner\" title=\"Johnny Lechner\">Johnny Lechner</a> has been attending the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Wisconsin%E2%80%93Whitewater\" title=\"University of Wisconsin\u2013Whitewater\">University of Wisconsin\u2013Whitewater</a> since 1994.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> He was scheduled to graduate in 2008 with multiple majors and minors, but continued into a 15th year of college.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Benjamin_Bolger\" title=\"Benjamin Bolger\">Benjamin Bolger</a>, who received his first four-year degree from the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Michigan\" title=\"University of Michigan\">University of Michigan</a>, claims to be the second most credentialed student in modern history, with twenty seven degrees.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Michael Nicholson has 30 degrees, including 19 master's degrees and one doctorate.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Milton De Jes\u00fas has been a student at the University of Puerto Rico since 1963. De Jes\u00fas was recently interviewed by the newspaper, since he is the only student at the campus that can make comparisons among the 2010 student strikes and the 1970s, 80s, 90s, and 2005 strikes. It is not certain if he has a degree.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Bruce Berry (1940-2014), notable for being a school <a href=\"/wiki/Crossing_guard\" title=\"Crossing guard\">crossing guard</a> having retired from a career including technical document translation for <a href=\"/wiki/Agfa-Gevaert\" title=\"Agfa-Gevaert\">Agfa-Gevaert</a>, working for the Post Office, and teaching, took his first degree from <a href=\"/wiki/Manchester_University\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Manchester University\">Manchester University</a> in 1963, and continued to study from the 1970s onwards, coming to possess several further Bachelor's and Master's degrees (from universities including <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Leeds\" title=\"University of Leeds\">Leeds</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_York\" title=\"University of York\">York</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Caen_Normandy\" title=\"University of Caen Normandy\">Normandy University, Caen</a>), as well as a Ph.D from <a href=\"/wiki/Leeds_Metropolitan_University\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Leeds Metropolitan University\">Leeds Metropolitan University</a>; he died before gaining his twelfth degree, another Ph.D. Fluent in several languages, he was also a Fellow of the <a href=\"/wiki/Chartered_Institute_of_Linguists\" title=\"Chartered Institute of Linguists\">Chartered Institute of Linguists</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Portrayal_in_media\">Portrayal in media</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Perpetual_student&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Portrayal in media\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The 2002 film <i><a href=\"/wiki/National_Lampoon%27s_Van_Wilder\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"National Lampoon&#39;s Van Wilder\">National Lampoon's Van Wilder</a></i> tells the story of Van Wilder, a popular student who has been in college for seven years, with no plans to graduate.\n</p><p>The <a href=\"/wiki/CW_Network\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"CW Network\">CW Network</a>'s program <i><a href=\"/wiki/Girlfriends_(U.S._TV_series)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Girlfriends (U.S. TV series)\">Girlfriends</a></i><span class=\"nowrap\" style=\"padding-left:0.1em;\">&#39;</span>s character, Lynn Searcy, remains in school and receives multiple post-graduate degrees.\n</p><p><i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Librarian_franchise\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"The Librarian franchise\">The Librarian</a></i> is a series of made-for-TV movies from TNT starring <a href=\"/wiki/Noah_Wyle\" title=\"Noah Wyle\">Noah Wyle</a> as a perpetual student who becomes a librarian protecting a secret collection of artifacts.\n</p><p>Diane, from the TV comedy <i><a href=\"/wiki/Cheers\" title=\"Cheers\">Cheers</a></i>.\n</p><p>The character of Daljit (\"DJ\") from the 2006 Bollywood movie <i><a href=\"/wiki/Rang_de_Basanti\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Rang de Basanti\">Rang de Basanti</a></i>.\n</p><p>The character of Peter Trophimof in <a href=\"/wiki/Anton_Chekhov\" title=\"Anton Chekhov\">Anton Chekhov</a>'s <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Cherry_Orchard\" title=\"The Cherry Orchard\">The Cherry Orchard</a></i>.\n</p><p><a href=\"/wiki/Rincewind\" title=\"Rincewind\">Rincewind</a>, the protagonist of many of <a href=\"/wiki/Terry_Pratchett\" title=\"Terry Pratchett\">Terry Pratchett</a>'s books.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Perpetual_student&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Sam Dillon (2005-11-10). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2005/11/10/national/10johnny.html?\">\"For One Student, a College Career Becomes a Career\"</a>. <i>The New York Times</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2010-05-22</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+New+York+Times&amp;rft.atitle=For+One+Student%2C+a+College+Career+Becomes+a+Career&amp;rft.date=2005-11-10&amp;rft.au=Sam+Dillon&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2005%2F11%2F10%2Fnational%2F10johnny.html%3F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3APerpetual+student\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Tess McEnroe. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.mlive.com/news/kalamazoo/index.ssf/2009/01/twentyseven_degrees_and_counti.html\">\"Twenty-seven degrees and counting: Kalamazoo man enjoys the 'freedom' of intellectual pursuits\"</a>. <i>Kalamazoo Gazette</i>. MLive.com<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2012-06-19</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Kalamazoo+Gazette&amp;rft.atitle=Twenty-seven+degrees+and+counting%3A+Kalamazoo+man+enjoys+the+%27freedom%27+of+intellectual+pursuits&amp;rft.au=Tess+McEnroe&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mlive.com%2Fnews%2Fkalamazoo%2Findex.ssf%2F2009%2F01%2Ftwentyseven_degrees_and_counti.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3APerpetual+student\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.mlive.com/news/kalamazoo/index.ssf/2009/01/twentyseven_degrees_and_counti.html\">Twenty-seven degrees and counting: Kalamazoo man enjoys the 'freedom' of intellectual pursuits</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">El Nuevo D\u00eda year xxxx, vol14449 page 6- also at: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=